{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"CreativeWork","name":"Vue.js generator","text":"\u003ch1\u003eVue.js generator\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCreate a Vue.js application using \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/vuejs/vue-cli\"\u003evue-cli\u003c/a\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ vue init webpack-simple my-app\n$ cd my-app\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInstall Vue Router, Vuex and babel-plugin-transform-builtin-extend (to allow extending bultin types like Error and Array):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ yarn add vue-router vuex babel-plugin-transform-builtin-extend babel-preset-es2015 babel-preset-stage-2 \n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInstall the generator globally:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ yarn global add @api-platform/client-generator\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eReference the Bootstrap CSS stylesheet in \u003ccode\u003eindex.html\u003c/code\u003e (optional):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-html\"\u003e  \u0026lt;!-- ... --\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;title\u0026gt;vue-generator\u0026lt;/title\u0026gt;\n\n    \u0026lt;link rel=\u0026#34;stylesheet\u0026#34; href=\u0026#34;https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css\u0026#34; integrity=\u0026#34;sha384-BVYiiSIFeK1dGmJRAkycuHAHRg32OmUcww7on3RYdg4Va+PmSTsz/K68vbdEjh4u\u0026#34; crossorigin=\u0026#34;anonymous\u0026#34;\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;/head\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;!-- ... --\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the app directory, generate the files for the resource you want:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ generate-api-platform-client https://demo.api-platform.com src/ --resource foo\n# Replace the URL by the entrypoint of your Hydra-enabled API\n# Omit the resource flag to generate files for all resource types exposed by the API\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe code is ready to be executed! Register the generated routes and store modules in the \u003ccode\u003emain.js\u003c/code\u003e file, here is an example:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-javascript\"\u003eimport Vue from \u0026#39;vue\u0026#39;\nimport Vuex from \u0026#39;vuex\u0026#39;;\nimport VueRouter from \u0026#39;vue-router\u0026#39;;\nimport App from \u0026#39;./App.vue\u0026#39;;\n\n// Replace \u0026#34;foo\u0026#34; by the name of the resource type\nimport foo from \u0026#39;./store/modules/foo/\u0026#39;;\nimport fooRoutes from \u0026#39;./routes/foo\u0026#39;;\n\nVue.use(Vuex);\nVue.use(VueRouter);\n\nconst store = new Vuex.Store({\n  modules: {\n    foo\n  }\n});\n\nconst router = new VueRouter({\n  mode: \u0026#39;history\u0026#39;,\n  routes: [\n      ...fooRoutes\n  ]\n});\n\nnew Vue({\n  el: \u0026#39;#app\u0026#39;,\n  store,\n  router,\n  render: h =\u0026gt; h(App)\n});\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMake sure to update the \u003ccode\u003e.babelrc\u003c/code\u003e file with the following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-javascript\"\u003e{\n  \u0026#34;presets\u0026#34;: [\n    [\u0026#34;es2015\u0026#34;, { \u0026#34;modules\u0026#34;: false }],\n    [\u0026#34;stage-2\u0026#34;]\n  ],\n  \u0026#34;plugins\u0026#34;: [\n    [\u0026#34;babel-plugin-transform-builtin-extend\u0026#34;, {\n      globals: [\u0026#34;Error\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;Array\u0026#34;]\n    }]\n  ]\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eReplace the \u003ccode\u003eApp.vue\u003c/code\u003e file with the following :\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-html\"\u003e\u0026lt;template\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;div class=\u0026#34;container\u0026#34;\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;nav\u0026gt;\n      \u0026lt;ul class=\u0026#34;nav nav-justified\u0026#34;\u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;!-- Replace Foo by your resource name --\u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;li class=\u0026#34;active\u0026#34;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;router-link :to=\u0026#34;{ name: \u0026#39;FooList\u0026#39; }\u0026#34; class=\u0026#34;active\u0026#34;\u0026gt;Foos\u0026lt;/router-link\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt;\n      \u0026lt;/ul\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;/nav\u0026gt;\n\n    \u0026lt;div\u0026gt;\n      \u0026lt;router-view\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/router-view\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;/div\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;/div\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/template\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePrevious chapter: \u003ca href=\"installation-and-usage.jsonld\"\u003eInstallation and Usage\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNext chapter: \u003ca href=\"troubleshooting.jsonld\"\u003eTroubleshooting\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","author":[{"@type":"Person","name":"Alain Hippolyte","email":"alain.hippolyte@gmail.com"},{"@type":"Person","name":"Piotr Synowiec","email":"mysiar@users.noreply.github.com"}],"dateCreated":"2017-09-26T00:20:56+02:00","dateModified":"2017-09-26T09:12:26+02:00"}